result.execSummary:
The defendant Timothy H Skinner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[ma] Case called at 3:46pm 
Defendant Timothy H Skinner in court.  Attorney Karl E Huebner in court for Timothy H Skinner.  Attorney Jeffrey Shock in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Maximum penalties are recited; Constitutional rights are reviewed; plea of " NO CONTEST " entered on Count #2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance is verified.  The Court accepts the plea, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #1 and #3. 

Sentencing recommendations/ arguments given by Counsel 

On Count #2, the Court imposes a sentence of 6 months jail, with Huber. The Court STAYS this sentence and places the Defendant on Probation for 18 months, with conditions:
--to serve 10 days in the Jefferson County Jail, with work-release privileges, to commence 9/18/22 at noon
---Mr. Skinner is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without non-prescribed controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of work-release privileges without further process.

--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment per Agent
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, or counseling per Agent
--no possession of any dangerous weapon
--complete Certified Batterers Intervention programming or Agent approved alternative
--no presence in bars, taverns, or liquor stores
--no contact with Witness 1 or Victim 1, except with written approval of Agent
--no acts or threats of violence
--no possession or ingestion of alcohol
--to comply with DNA sample provision 
--payment of costs, fees and surcharges
